        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 1:49AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 147 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms in
eastern Jones and northern Shackelford counties, moving southeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nugent, Lueders, Mccarty Lake, Clyde, Baird, Big Country Baptist
Assembly, Us-283 Near The Callahan-
Shackelford County Line, Moran, Us-180 Near The Shackelford-
Stephens County Line, The Intersection Of Us-
180 And Farm Road 600, Ibex, and Albany.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 293 and 309.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
